This app is intentionally pull-based with no realtime subscriptions.

## Rules
- Never use Supabase realtime (no `supabase.channel()`, no websocket listeners, no `on('postgres_changes', ...)`)
- Never implement optimistic UI updates
- Never push data to the client — all data is fetched on demand
- UI refreshes on navigation or explicit user action (e.g. pull-to-refresh) only
- All time-sensitive logic (e.g. cutoff scoring) runs server-side on a schedule, not triggered by client actions

## Rationale
- Submission model is once-per-day; realtime updates provide no meaningful UX benefit
- Leaderboard results are intentionally hidden until cutoff or full submission — push updates would undermine this
- Keeps client logic simple and the architecture easy to reason about
- Explicitly agreed upon with the client as a design requirement

## Acceptable patterns
- `supabase.from(...).select(...)` queries on component mount or user-triggered refresh
- Server-side scheduled functions (e.g. Supabase Edge Functions via cron) for cutoff processing
- Returning fresh data after a mutation by re-fetching, not by updating local state directly
